  "prompt": "What is the best gift a student can give to teacher in graduation?",
  "response": "The best gifts for teachers during graduation often depend on the individual teacher and your relationship with them. However, here are some thoughtful and appreciated options:\n\n1. Heartfelt Handwritten Letter\n- Express genuine gratitude\n- Share specific memories and impact they had on you\n- Describe how they influenced your life/education\n\n2. Personalized Gifts\n- Customized photo frame with class picture\n- Personalized notebook or planner\n- Engraved pen or desk item\n\n3. Meaningful Keepsakes\n- Scrapbook with class memories\n- Signed class yearbook\n- Group photo signed by all students\n\n4. Professional Gifts\n- Gift card to bookstore or coffee shop\n- Quality stationery set\n- Elegant desk accessories\n\n5. Practical Gifts\n- Teaching resources\n- Classroom supplies\n- Educational books\n\n6. Sentimental Gifts\n- Inspirational quote artwork\n- Commemorative plaque\n- Small symbolic gift representing their teaching\n\n7. Group Gifts\n- Collective gift from entire class\n- Pooled funds for more significant present\n- Meaningful group gesture\n\n8. Experience Gifts\n- Gift certificate for professional development\n- Contribution to classroom resources\n\nRemember, the most important aspect is sincerity and showing genuine appreciation for their dedication and guidance.",
